        <!-- Project Summary -->
        <section class="mt-20 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-12">
                <div class="text-center md:text-left">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-600 mb-2">The Problem</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-500">
                        Existing social media platforms often lead to digital isolation. Users crave genuine, real-world connections but lack a tool to discover and join spontaneous local activities easily.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="text-center md:text-left">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-600 mb-2">Our Solution</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-500">
                        An app that uses location and user interests to suggest or create small, local "micro-events." This encourages spontaneous meetups for activities like coffee, sports, or study groups.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="text-center md:text-left">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-600 mb-2">The Outcome</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-500">
                        This concept lays the groundwork for a platform that fosters community and combats loneliness. Key outcomes include a detailed PRD, user flow diagrams, and initial low-fidelity wireframes.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

